[104.594109, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100mвқҜ Create a new persistent tool named count-words that takes a file path and returns the number of\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K  whitespace-separated words in that file's content.\u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92mвң“\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(60446 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(55.6s)\u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mTask: author a persistent tool `count-words`. Prior turn established only \u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m`user$count-lines` and `user$shout-test` exist, so no collision. I'll compose `read-file` \u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mand count non-whitespace runs via `re-seq #\"\\S+\"` (handles empty files вҶ’ 0). Dry-run with \u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mtools$validate first, sampling against an existing file (~/.brainyard/BRAINYARD.md) to \u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mconfirm behavior before tools$create.\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36mвҶ’\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mtools$validate\u001b[0m({\"name\" \"count-words\", \"body\" \"(fn [args] (let [path (:pa...): called \u001b[2mвҶ’\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 9ms, 90 chars\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92mвң“\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b"]
